    {
      "id": "b322fdf6297996a8a5c3e83ac151753aa66b4819",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 284,
        "name": "Emoly Liu",
        "email": "emoly@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "liuying_emoly"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-30 13:33:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nIn the old lustre version, lprocfs_rd_fstype() was called by mds, mgs, obdfilter and others. But now, each component has its own rd_fstype function, e.g. ll_rd_fstype(), lprocfs_ofd_rd_fstype() and lprocfs_osd_rd_fstype().\r\n\r\nI don't mind to link osd's there if we can't have a proper lprocfs_mgs_rd_fstype(). \r\n\r\nOne suggestion: In order to avoid such error, can we add a sanity.sh test to check all the readable lustre proc entries?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
